sentences: Marti Epstein (born November 25, 1959) is an American composer.
Epstein was born in Denver, Colorado in 1959.
She began composition studies in 1977 while still in high school with Professor Robert Beadell at the University of Nebraska.

She earned degrees from the University of Colorado (Bachelor of Music in Composition, summa cum laude, 1982) and Boston University (Master of Music in Composition, 1984; Doctor of Musical Arts in Composition, 1989).

She earned degrees from the University of Colorado (Bachelor of Music in Composition, summa cum laude, 1982) and Boston University (Master of Music in Composition, 1984; Doctor of Musical Arts in Composition, 1989).
In April 2020, she was awarded a Guggenheim Fellowship for music composition.
In 1992 she was invited by the City of Munich to compose her puppet opera, Hero und Leander, for the 1992 Munich Biennale for New Music Theater.
